    "body": "If I'm not mistaken we can acheive this using flexbox properties. I have updated the pinned message variation here: #17078.\r\n\r\nVariation| Before | After\r\n-|-|-\r\nShort name | ![Simulator Screenshot - iPhone 11 Pro - 2023-08-22 at 12 34 26](https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/assets/19279756/237bae21-bdff-42bd-a055-e5a718d22019) | ![Simulator Screenshot - iPhone 11 Pro - 2023-08-22 at 12 36 00](https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/assets/19279756/8090a6d6-b555-401b-b374-4def56dfdbcb)\r\nLong name | ![Simulator Screenshot - iPhone 11 Pro - 2023-08-22 at 12 35 03](https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/assets/19279756/16dd45fc-7df9-4ada-8955-bd3e90a6e8fe) | ![Simulator Screenshot - iPhone 11 Pro - 2023-08-22 at 12 36 41](https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/assets/19279756/0c55257c-2715-4ef3-bad3-81ab6b6e65eb)\r\n\r\n@alwx I couldn't find a system messages component variant in Figma that accommodates long names within a single line, where we'd need to truncate the name. It might be a good idea to consult the design team before proceeding further with this issue. Have you already checked with the design team about this?\r\n\r\ncc: @flexsurfer ",
